        extension: "Accelerator Mass Spectrometry (AMS) allows ¹⁴C dating of samples as small as a milligram by directly counting ¹⁴C atoms relative to ¹²C atoms using the same principles as conventional mass spectrometry (ionisation, acceleration, deflection by m/z) but at much higher energies. AMS has revolutionised archaeology, allowing dating of single seeds, individual hairs, or fragments of medieval manuscripts."
