        problem: "A synthesis protocol refers to '3-methylpentane' as the solvent. A student accidentally uses '2-methylpentane' instead. Explain, using IUPAC numbering rules, why these are different compounds and predict which has the higher boiling point.",
        application: "3-methylpentane: parent chain = pentane (5 carbons), methyl substituent at C3. 2-methylpentane: methyl branch at C2 — more branching, more compact shape, smaller surface area. 3-methylpentane (less branched, more extended) has larger surface area, stronger London forces → higher boiling point.",
