        problem: "A forensic sample of heptane is combusted under oxygen-limited conditions. Predict the products and write a balanced equation for incomplete combustion producing carbon monoxide only (no soot).",
        application: "Incomplete combustion: C₇H₁₆ + [O₂, limited] → CO + H₂O. Balance: carbon → 7CO; hydrogen → 8H₂O; oxygen: 7+8=15 oxygen atoms on right → 15/2 O₂. Multiply by 2: 2C₇H₁₆ + 15O₂ → 14CO + 16H₂O. CO is the forensic marker for oxygen-limited combustion and is toxic at low concentrations.",
